  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two systems, labeled “System 1” and “System 2.” Each system shows three small charged spheres at the corners of an equilateral triangle. In each of the systems, point C is located at the center of the triangle, and the sides of the triangle have length s. In system 1, the bottom left sphere has charge negative uppercase Q, the bottom right sphere has charge positive uppercase Q, and the top middle sphere has charge positive uppercase Q. In system 2, the bottom left sphere has charge negative uppercase Q, the bottom right sphere has charge negative uppercase Q, and the top middle sphere has charge positive uppercase Q.&nbsp;\" src=\"/images/7b0905b50143ea191000800bb9764729.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In each of the two systems shown in the figure, three small, charged spheres are arranged at the corners of an equilateral triangle having side length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s\"><math alttext=\"s\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>s</mi></math></span></span> and center located at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span>. The charges on the spheres are as indicated in the figure and are all of the same magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase Q\"><math alttext=\"uppercase Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span>. The two systems differ in the sign of the charge located at the lower right corner. How do the electric potential energies <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub 1\"><math alttext=\"U sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub 2\"><math alttext=\"U sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> of systems <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> compare, and what evidence or reasoning supports the claim?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
